JavaScript vs ECMAScript

ECMAScript is specification and JavaScript programming language that confirm specification
JS stands for JavaScript.
It is a programming language that is commonly used for web development. 
JavaScript allows developers to add interactivity and dynamic features to websites. 
It is a versatile language that can be used both on the client-side (in the browser) and on the server-side (with the help of Node.js).